summer country
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a high-country farming term for an area that is usable in summer as pasture, but not in winter.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:winter country
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 13/8/1938
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 13
Edition:
Quote: "In those cases where there is no natural boundary between winter and summer country it would on many runs be practicable to fence off the unsafe country, with a view to ensuring that sheep mustered down on to the winter country in the autumn could not drift back between storms on to unsafe country and be lost, were it not for the heavy expense involved in fencing ..."
