Date: 0/0/1966
Source: Boss's Story, The
Author:  NEWTON
Vol / Page: 189
Edition:
Quote: <i>Summer country</i>: high-country run comprises summer and winter country. The former is the higher or shady country which carries a lot of snow during the winter and is then uunsafe for stock. Winter country is the lower and sunnier country on which sheep can safely be carried during the winter.
Notes: (Gloss.)

